math.geom2d
Class Parabola2D

java.lang.Object
  math.geom2d.Parabola2D
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.awt.Shape, Conic2D, ContinuousCurve2D, Curve2D, OrientedCurve2D, Shape2D, SmoothCurve2D
public class Parabola2D
extends java.lang.Object
implements SmoothCurve2D, Conic2D, OrientedCurve2D

A parabola, defined by its vertex, its orientation, and its pedal. Orientation is defined as the orientation of derivative at vertex point, with the second derivative pointing to the top.

Parametric representation is used:

x(t)=t

y(t)=t^2/(4*p)

where p is the parameter of the parabola, i.e. the distance between the vertex and the focus. This is a signed parameter (negative p makes the parabola points to opposite side).

Author:
dlegland
